[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer report reveals a segmentation fault [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSEGV[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m caused by a write to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maddress [0m[1;36m0x0[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnull dereference[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The crash occurs in [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_response` when invoked by the fuzzing harness function[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`test_server`. The issue is classified as a null-dereference vulnerability [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mSCARINESS [0m[1;36m10[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Issue type**  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The program attempts a WRITE memory access at address [0m[1;36m0x000000000000[0m[39m, indicating [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma null pointer dereference.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Crash details**  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Sanitizer output: “ERROR: AddressSanitizer: SEGV on unknown address [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m0x000000000000[0m[39m”  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The faulting instruction pointer and stack trace show the failure inside [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_response` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlibfreerdp/core/freerdp.[0m[1;92mc:1458:16[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - This function is called from `test_server` in TestFuzzCoreServer.c [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m83[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich in turn is invoked by the fuzzing entry point `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Vulnerability classification**  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Memory safety violation: null-dereference leading to write access at address [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mzero.  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Denial-of-service potential, as the crash aborts execution.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Key observations**  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. The null write occurs before any user-managed memory is allocated or validated[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the target function.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. The fuzz harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`test_server` [0m[35m/[0m[39m `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m merely supplies [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marbitrary input; it is not responsible for the invalid memory use but serves as the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry point.  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. No additional AddressSanitizer diagnostics are available [0m[1;39m([0m[39m“AddressSanitizer [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcan not provide additional info”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Areas for further inspection**  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  To fully understand the issue, review the following components:  [0m                 [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer run over the FreeRDP core library uncovered a null‐pointer [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrite in the function `freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_response`. The user’s patch [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madded input validation in that function—checking for non‐NULL `data`, a valid [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstream object [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`s`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and a non‐NULL `mcs` handle, returning `FALSE` on invalid [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minputs. After applying the patch, the same SEGV on address [0m[1;36m0x0[0m[39m still occurs inside [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_response`, indicating that the null‐dereference issue [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpersists.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer reports a segmentation fault [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSEGV[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m caused by a write access to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maddress [0m[1;36m0x0[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnull page[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Stack trace pinpoints the fault at:[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - `freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_response` in `libfreerdp/core/freerdp.[0m[1;92mc:1458:16[0m[39m`.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Called by `test_server` in the fuzz harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`TestFuzzCoreServer.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvokes `mcs_recv_connect_response`.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The error is classified as “SCARINESS: [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnull-deref[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m”.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No additional information is provided by AddressSanitizer beyond the null‐pointer[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrite.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Important Observations[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash originates in `freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_response`, which wraps [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mcs_recv_connect_response`.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m calls into this function, supplying[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marbitrary input data and size.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The null‐pointer write suggests that some internal pointer or structure was not [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproperly initialized before being dereferenced or written to.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe user added defensive checks at the top of [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_response`:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwStream sbuffer = [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwStream* s = [0m[1;35mStream_StaticConstInit[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&sbuffer, data, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[39m* Validate inputs to prevent null dereference in release builds *[0m[35m/[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!data && size > [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return FALSE;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!s[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return FALSE;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrdpMcs* mcs = [0m[1;35mtest_mcs_new[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!mcs[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return FALSE;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBOOL result = [0m[1;35mmcs_recv_connect_response[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmcs, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mtest_mcs_free[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmcs[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturn result;[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The checks ensure `data` is non‐NULL for `size > [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m`, that the stream [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minitialization returned a valid pointer, and that `mcs` was allocated successfully.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All original `WINPR_ASSERT` calls were replaced with explicit `if`‐based returns.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Result[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After recompiling with the added checks, the crash still reproduces.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer output shows the fault still occurs at the same PC inside [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_response`, indicating the null dereference happens [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mafter these input checks or within deeper logic not protected by the new checks.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The stack trace remains unchanged apart from updated line numbers.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Further Investigation[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_response**  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Examine all pointer dereferences within this function, not just the early [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minitialization.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Identify any calls that assume internal fields of `mcs` or `s` are non‐NULL [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mafter the initial checks.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **mcs_recv_connect_response**  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Inspect how it parses the stream and whether it writes through uninitialized [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointers or misinterprets length fields.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Verify boundary checks on stream reads/writes.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **test_mcs_new [0m[35m/[0m[39m test_mcs_free**  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm that `test_mcs_new` fully initializes the `rdpMcs` structure [0m[1;39m([0m[39mall [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointers and sub‐structures[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure there are no hidden NULL pointers inside the newly allocated `mcs` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mobject.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Stream Utilities [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwStream[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Check that `Stream_StaticConstInit` always returns a valid stream for any [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcombination of `data` and `size` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mincluding zero‐length input[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Look for any operations on the stream pointer or buffer that might write at [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffset zero.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Fuzzer Harness Code**  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - While not the root cause, review how `test_server` and [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` feed data into `freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_response`.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure that the harness does not rely on undefined behavior elsewhere that [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcould corrupt pointers or memory.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBy tracing through these components together, the precise null dereference site can[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe located and understood in context.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m557[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mper_write_number_of_sets[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m558[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn FALSE;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m559[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* UserData::value present + select h221NonStandard [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m560[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mper_write_choice[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, [0m[1;36m0xC0[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m563[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mper_write_octet_string[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, h221_sc_key, [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m,[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m564[0m[39m:    [0m[39m                            [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[39m* h221NonStandard, server-to-client H.[0m[1;36m221[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mkey, [0m[32m"McDn"[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m565[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn FALSE;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m567[0m[39m:    [0m[39mconst size_t pos = [0m[1;35mStream_GetPosition[0m[1;39m([0m[39muserData[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m569[0m[39m:    [0m[39mreturn [0m[1;35mper_write_octet_string[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, [0m[1;35mStream_Buffer[0m[1;39m([0m[39muserData[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT16[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mpos,[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m570[0m[39m:    [0m[39m                              [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; [0m[35m/[0m[39m* array of server data blocks *[0m[35m/[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m571[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m574[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m575[0m[39m:    [0m[39mreturn [0m[1;35mStream_SafeSeek[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m577[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m578:B[0m[39mOOL [0m[1;35mgcc_read_client_data_blocks[0m[1;39m([0m[39mwStream* s, rdpMcs* mcs, UINT16 length[0m[1;39m)[0m        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblockLength - [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m28[0m[39m:#define TAG [0m[1;35mFREERDP_TAG[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"core.tpkt"[0m[1;39m)[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m29[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m30[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m31[0m[39m: * TPKTs are defined in:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m32[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m33[0m[39m: * [0m[4;94mhttp://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc1006/[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m34[0m[39m: * RFC [0m[1;36m1006[0m[39m - ISO Transport Service on top of the TCP[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m35[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m36[0m[39m: * [0m[4;94mhttp://www.itu.int/rec/T-REC-T.123/[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m37[0m[39m: * ITU-T T.[0m[1;36m123[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m01[0m[39m/[0m[1;36m2007[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m - Network-specific data protocol stacks for multimedia [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconferencing[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m38[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m39[0m[39m: *       TPKT Header[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m40[0m[39m: *  ____________________   byte[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m41[0m[39m: * |                    |[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m42[0m[39m: * |     [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mversion[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m    |   [0m[1;36m1[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m43[0m[39m: * |____________________|[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m44[0m[39m: * |                    |[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m45[0m[39m: * |      Reserved      |   [0m[1;36m2[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m46[0m[39m: * |____________________|[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m47[0m[39m: * |                    |[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m48[0m[39m: * |    Length [0m[1;39m([0m[39mMSB[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m    |   [0m[1;36m3[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m49[0m[39m: * |____________________|[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m50[0m[39m: * |                    |[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m51[0m[39m: * |    Length [0m[1;39m([0m[39mLSB[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m    |   [0m[1;36m4[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m52[0m[39m: * |____________________|[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m53[0m[39m: * |                    |[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m54[0m[39m: * |     X.[0m[1;36m224[0m[39m TPDU     |   [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m - ?[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m55[0m[39m: *          [0m[33m...[0m[39m.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m56[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m57[0m[39m: * A TPKT header is of fixed length [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m, and the following X.[0m[1;36m224[0m[39m TPDU is at least [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthree bytes long.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m58[0m[39m: * Therefore, the minimum TPKT length is [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m, and the maximum TPKT length is [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m65535[0m[39m. Because the TPKT[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m59[0m[39m: * length includes the TPKT header [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the maximum X.[0m[1;36m224[0m[39m TPDU length is [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m65531[0m[39m.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m60[0m[39m: *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m61[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m62[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m63[0m[39m: * Verify if a packet has valid TPKT header.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m64[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m65[0m[39m: * @param s A stream to read from[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m66[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m67[0m[39m: * @return \b TRUE for success, \b FALSE otherwise[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m68[0m[39m: *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m69[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m70[0m[39m:int [0m[1;35mtpkt_verify_header[0m[1;39m([0m[39mwStream* s[0m[1;39m)[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m71[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m72[0m[39m:     [0m[39mBYTE version = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1458[0m[39m:   [0m[39mBOOL result = [0m[1;35mmcs_recv_connect_response[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmcs, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1459[0m[39m:   [0m[1;35mtest_mcs_free[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmcs[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1460[0m[39m:   [0m[39mreturn result;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1461[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibfreerdp/core/freerdp.[0m[1;92mc:1446[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1461[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m1446:B[0m[39mOOL [0m[1;35mfreerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_response[0m[1;39m([0m[39mconst BYTE* data, size_t size[0m[1;39m)[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1447[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1448[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1449[0m[39m:   [0m[39mwStream sbuffer = [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1450[0m[39m:   [0m[39mwStream* s = [0m[1;35mStream_StaticConstInit[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&sbuffer, data, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1451[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1452[0m[39m:   [0m[1;35mWINPR_ASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata || [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1453[0m[39m:   [0m[1;35mWINPR_ASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1454[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1455[0m[39m:   [0m[39mrdpMcs* mcs = [0m[1;35mtest_mcs_new[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1456[0m[39m:   [0m[1;35mWINPR_ASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmcs[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1457[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1458[0m[39m:   [0m[39mBOOL result = [0m[1;35mmcs_recv_connect_response[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmcs, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1459[0m[39m:   [0m[1;35mtest_mcs_free[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmcs[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1460[0m[39m:   [0m[39mreturn result;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1461[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Reapply and extend input validation in freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_response:[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. At the very top of the function, before initializing the stream, insert a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguard that returns FALSE whenever the input pointer is NULL or the size is zero:[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!data || size == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            return FALSE;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Keep the existing defensive checks from the last patch:[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        wStream sbuffer = [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        wStream* s = [0m[1;35mStream_StaticConstInit[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&sbuffer, data, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!s[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            return FALSE;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        rdpMcs* mcs = [0m[1;35mtest_mcs_new[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!mcs[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            return FALSE;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Proceed to call mcs_recv_connect_response and free the mcs handle as before.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Justification:[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The AddressSanitizer reports a null‐pointer write because, when [0m[33mdata[0m[39m==NULL and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [33msize[0m[39m==[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, Stream_StaticConstInit produces a wStream whose buffer/pointer is NULL. [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe downstream parser [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtpkt_read_header and related routines[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m then writes to or [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreads from s->pointer, triggering a write at address [0m[1;36m0x0[0m[39m.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By rejecting zero‐length or NULL‐buffer inputs immediately, we guarantee that [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ms->pointer is always non‐NULL when mcs_recv_connect_response is called, thus [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meliminating the null‐pointer write.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This validation is local to freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_response. No harness [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode, parser code, or external libraries are modified.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Preservation of existing logic:[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Valid inputs [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnon‐NULL data with size>[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m still flow through the same parsing [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand validation logic.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing tests and fuzz harnesses will simply get FALSE for empty or NULL [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minput, which correctly indicates “not a valid MCS create response.”[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The original assertions [0m[1;39m([0m[39mWINPR_ASSERT[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m have already been replaced by explicit [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturns in the previous patch; we preserve those checks and just add one more to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcover the missing NULL/zero‐size case.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Side effects and mitigation:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Inputs of size zero [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhich have no meaningful protocol content[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are now [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimmediately dropped. This is aligned with the function’s purpose of validating a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwell‐formed MCS create response.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No valid protocol exchange should use zero‐length payloads here, so no [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlegitimate behavior is lost.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If necessary, the minimum accepted size could be raised to the TPKT minimum [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m7[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to catch other malformed cases, but the zero‐size guard addresses the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcritical null‐write crash.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. References in codebase:[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_response is the single entrypoint for the fuzzer [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mharness; all validation lives here.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stream_StaticConstInit/Stream_StaticInit assignments assume a non‐NULL buffer [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer for safe parsing.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Earlier patches already removed WINPR_ASSERTs for release builds; this [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maddition completes the input‐sanitization coverage.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo further changes to harness, parser utilities, or external code are required. [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis minimal patch closes the null‐pointer write while preserving existing [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctionality and test coverage.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     `freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_response`, now at line [0m[1;36m1462[0m[39m.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash still happens during the call to `[0m[1;35mmcs_recv_connect_response[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmcs, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, indicating the root cause remains in the parsing logic invoked by that call [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrather than in the early checks.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Further Investigation Areas  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_response [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlibfreerdp/core/freerdp.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Examine how the `wStream` is consumed. Are there subsequent stream reads or [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrites without bounds checking?  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stream_StaticConstInit and wStream API  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Verify that initializing a stream over arbitrary data cannot leave internal [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointers NULL or cause out-of-bounds pointers.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - mcs_recv_connect_response [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlibfreerdp/core/mcs.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Inspect all writes to the stream or to internal MCS structures [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchannel arrays[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - test_mcs_new [0m[35m/[0m[39m test_mcs_free [0m[1;39m([0m[39mCore test helpers[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Ensure the returned `rdpMcs` object is fully initialized for all fields used[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mby the parser.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - MCS create response parsing routines  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Check length fields, pointer arithmetic, and memory writes for missing [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidity checks.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA holistic view requires tracing the data flow from the initial stream setup [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthrough every layer of the MCS connect‐response parser to pinpoint the unchecked [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdereference.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPRIuz [0m[32m" bytes with [0m[32mtype[0m[32m=%s"[0m[39m,[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m891[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m          rest, [0m[1;35mgcc_block_type_string[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtype, buffer, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuffer[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m894[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m895[0m[39m:    [0m[39mreturn TRUE;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
