[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Eliminate the unsafe “[0m[1;36m0x42[0m[39m” branch in mcs_recv_connect_response  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In libfreerdp/core/freerdp.c, locate the code block:[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mber_read_application_tag[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, [0m[1;36m0x42[0m[39m, &length[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         … posix_memalign [0m[35m/[0m[39m mprotect [0m[35m/[0m[39m jump-to-heap … [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return TRUE;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     else[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mStream_Rewind[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Remove this entire `if`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`else` branch. It performs unchecked heap writes and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man arbitrary function jump, leading to null‐pointer writes or out‐of‐bounds writes [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munder fuzzed inputs. Its removal does not break valid MCS Connect‐Response parsing,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbecause the standard path [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtag MCS_TYPE_CONNECT_RESPONSE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m immediately follows.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Harden mcs_recv_connect_response with strict bounds checks  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   In libfreerdp/core/freerdp.c, after the `Stream_StaticConstInit` and allocation [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks already added:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Validate the TPKT length against the input buffer:  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      UINT16 tlength = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mtpkt_read_header[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, &tlength[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || tlength < MIN_EXPECTED_MCS_PDU_LENGTH [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m||[0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          tlength > size_of_input_stream[0m[1;39m)[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return FALSE;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Define `MIN_EXPECTED_MCS_PDU_LENGTH` to be the smallest valid MCS packet [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39me.g., header + minimal ACL + domain parameters[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. After reading the BER application tag for MCS connect response:  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      size_t resLength = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mber_read_application_tag[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, MCS_TYPE_CONNECT_RESPONSE, &resLength[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ||[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          resLength > [0m[1;35mStream_GetRemainingLength[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return FALSE;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. After reading the octet‐string tag that delimits the [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconference‐create‐response blob:  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      size_t blobLength = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mber_read_octet_string_tag[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, &blobLength[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ||[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          blobLength > [0m[1;35mStream_GetRemainingLength[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return FALSE;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Harden per‐block parsing in gcc_read_server_data_blocks  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   In libfreerdp/core/gcc.c, around the loop in `gcc_read_server_data_blocks`:[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```c[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   while [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset < length[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       UINT16 blockLength = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[35m/[0m[39m* read type/length header *[0m[35m/[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mgcc_read_user_data_header[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, &type, &blockLength[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           return FALSE;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[35m/[0m[39m* guard against underflow or over‐large blocks *[0m[35m/[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mblockLength < USER_DATA_[0m[1;33mHEAD[0m[39mER_SIZE ||[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m blockLength - USER_DATA_[0m[1;33mHEAD[0m[39mER_SIZE > [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mStream_GetRemainingLength[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           return FALSE;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[35m/[0m[39m* initialize substream *[0m[35m/[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       holdp = [0m[1;35mStream_Pointer[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       sub = [0m[1;35mStream_StaticInit[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&subbuffer, holdp, blockLength - [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mUSER_DATA_[0m[1;33mHEAD[0m[39mER_SIZE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mStream_SafeSeek[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, blockLength - USER_DATA_[0m[1;33mHEAD[0m[39mER_SIZE[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           return FALSE;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       offset += blockLength;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[35m/[0m[39m* dispatch on type … *[0m[35m/[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Define `USER_DATA_[0m[1;33mHEAD[0m[39mER_SIZE` [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to match how MCS user‐data [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheaders are parsed.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This prevents `blockLength - [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m` from underflowing and ensures the substream is[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monly as large as the remaining bytes.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Validate DomainParameters length in mcs_read_domain_parameters  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   In libfreerdp/core/mcs.c [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhere `mcs_read_domain_parameters` is implemented[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madd:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```c[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   UINT16 parmsLength = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mper_read_length[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, &parmsLength[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ||[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       parmsLength != EXPECTED_DOMAIN_PARMS_LENGTH ||[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       parmsLength > [0m[1;35mStream_GetRemainingLength[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return FALSE;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[35m/[0m[39m* then read each UINT32 field in DomainParameters *[0m[35m/[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Set `EXPECTED_DOMAIN_PARMS_LENGTH` to the known fixed length [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m[1;36m28[0m[39m bytes [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor seven UINT32 fields[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This ensures a malformed length tag cannot cause out‐of‐bounds reads/writes.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Preserve existing logic and API  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Do not alter any harness or test code [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`TestFuzzCoreServer.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Do not modify external libraries, utility functions, or remove functionality [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mused by valid RDP connections.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - On every early‐exit path [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`return FALSE;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, ensure any allocated `mcs` object [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis freed to avoid leaks:  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     BOOL result = [0m[1;35mmcs_recv_connect_response[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmcs, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mtest_mcs_free[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmcs[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     return result;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mExplanation:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Removing the obfuscated [0m[1;36m0x42[0m[39m branch removes the undefined behavior and arbitrary [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrites/callouts that triggered the null‐pointer write under fuzzed inputs.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The added bounds checks at each stage of parsing enforce that any length or size [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfield read from untrusted data cannot exceed the actual buffer length. Under any [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmalformed or adversarial inputs, the code now cleanly fails [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`return FALSE`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m rather[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthan dereferencing null or writing out of bounds.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The stream‐based safety [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`Stream_SafeSeek`, `Stream_GetRemainingLength`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mleveraged to tightly guard substream operations.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- By checking that domain parameters have exactly the expected length, we close a [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mgap where a malformed length tag could lead to under‐ or over‐reads of the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`DomainParameters` struct.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This patch strategy does not affect valid MCS create response flows [0m[1;39m([0m[39mall valid [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRDP servers send well‐formed tags and lengths[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, so existing functionality and tests[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremain unchanged.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Potential side effects: valid but unusually large user‐data blocks exceeding [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhalf‐megabyte will now be refused. In practice, MCS create responses are small [0m[1;39m([0m[39ma [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfew kilobytes at most[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, so this safeguard will not affect legitimate sessions.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- We reference the existing use of `Stream_SafeSeek` in [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`gcc_read_server_data_blocks` and the manual length checks already inserted in [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_response` as a template for systematic bounds [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39menforcement throughout the parsing chain.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
